  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2022-09-29",
    "date": "2022-10-20T17:17:35Z",
    "text": "Prevent Family Fire Act of 2022\n\nThis bill allows a new business-related tax credit, through 2030, for 10% of the amount of\u00a0the first retail sale of a safe firearm storage device. The amount upon which the credit is based may not exceed $400.\n\nA safe firearm storage device is a device that (1) is designed and marketed to deny unauthorized access to, or rendering inoperable, a firearm or ammunition; and (2) is secured by a combination lock, key lock, or lock based on biometric information."
